This paper focuses on the dynamics of participation in Q&A communities, specifically on Stack Overflow, and investigates factors that can increase the chance of eliciting a successful answer to technical questions. The paper uses a quantitative analysis of a large dataset of Stack Overflow questions, as well as qualitative analysis and a survey. The paper touches on topics related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC), natural language processing (cs.CL), software engineering (cs.SE), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, the paper's main focus is on the community aspect of Stack Overflow, which makes the category of cybernetics (cs.CY) the most likely primary category.
